                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/chee-314" class="program-course-title">
              CHEE 314 Fluid Mechanics (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-20186" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Chemical Engineering (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/609">Faculty of Engineering</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Chemical Engineering              : Fluid properties; dimensional analysis; drag; packed/fluidized beds; macroscopic energy balances, Bernoulli's equation and linear momentum theorem; flowmeters, pipeline systems, non-Newtonian fluids, microscopic balances leading to continuity and Navier-Stokes equations; boundary layer approximation; turbulence. Laboratory exercises.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:              There are no professors associated with this course for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>(3-2-4)</li>
              <li>Prerequisite: CHEE 204.</li>
              <li>Corequisite: MATH 264.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

